definition.value: A member of the class of thiazepinedicarboxylic acids that is 2,5,6,7-tetrahydro-1,4-thiazepine substituted by carboxy groups at positions 3 and 5.
A member of the class of imidazopyrimidines that is imidazo[1,2-a]pyrimidine substituted by a [4-(3,4-dichlorophenyl)piperazin-1-yl]acetyl group at position 3.
A cholestanoid that is cholesta-5,24-diene substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 3. It is an intermediate metabolite obtained during the synthesis of cholesterol.
A malonate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the 6-hydroxy group of trans-rhaponticin with the carboxy group of malonic acid.
The hydrochloride salt of L-778,123. It is a dual inhibitor of FPTase and GGPTase-I (IC50 of 2nM and 98nm, respectively) and exhibits anti-cancer properties.

An organic heterotricyclic compound that is (4aR,10bR)-3,4,4a,5,6,10b-hexahydro-2H-naphtho[1,2-b][1,4]oxazine substituted by propyl and hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 9, respectively. It is a potent dopamine D2-receptor agonist and its hydrochloride salt was under clinical development by Merck & Co as a potential antiparkinsonian agent (now discontinued).
This drug is a zinc metalloendopeptidase inhibitor with cardiovascular effects similar to ACE inhibitors.
A tertiary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of naxagolide arising from the protonation of the tertiary amino group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A hydrate that is the decahydrate form of sodium diphosphate.

A  synthetic phosphate-linked oligosaccharide analogue that is a chimeric oligosaccharide antigen (ST19AF) comprised of one repeating unit each of the pneumococcal polysaccharides of Streptococcus pneumoniae serotypes 19A and 19F (ST19A and ST19F; CHEBI:62986 and CHEBI:62687). A terminal C5-amino linker enables site-specific conjugation to a carrier protein, to induce protective antibodies against both serotypes.
A member of the class of formamidines that is lisinopril in which the primary amino group is substituted by an {(E)-[(4-hydroxyphenyl)imino]methyl}amino group. It is a potent ACE inhibitor.

A hydroxycoumarin that is 4-hydroxycoumarin which is substituted at position 3 by a 4-azidobenzyl group. It is a photoaffinity probe used in the identification of warfarin-binding proteins present in mammalian tissue.

A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid that is quinoline substituted by 2'-fluoro[1,1'-biphenyl]-4-yl, methyl, carboxy and fluoro groups at positions 2, 3, 4, and 6, respectively. It is an inhibitor of dihydroorotate dehydrogenase, an enzyme that is required for de novo pyrimidine biosynthesis. The compound exhibits antineoplastic and antiviral properties.
A lipopeptide formed by substitution of the amino terminal hydrogen of a glycylpeptide by a tetradecanoyl group.
A 4-(trimethylammonio)but-2-enoic acid with a (E)-configuration at the double bond.
A non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid that is serine in which the alcoholic hydroxy group has been formally oxidised to the corresponding formyl group.
A member of the class of formamides that is formamide in which the amino hydrogens are replaced by methyl groups.
